    {
      "id": "nqOx8cdGRhq_c-NU4ZGSM",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3856.6557202074196,
      "y": 1279.394000525505,
      "width": 1148.599365234375,
      "height": 925,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bEJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1745972832,
      "version": 1466,
      "versionNonce": 2004600416,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771774864052,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "deep dive 2: scalability for popular events\n* take a step back & think about the perspective of users\n1. talk through what the client has to do when buying a ticket\n2. 1st instance is accurate representation of avail seats\n3. in a few moments, especially popz events, view can go stale quickly\n4. can make seat map availablity in real time\n\nin real time seat map\nsoln1: long polling\nkeep long polling the server\ncheap\nez to implement\nespecially when users are not on there for a long time (few seconds to mins)\n\nsoln2: SSE\nnot similar to implementation as long polling\nreduce the overhead of having to keep polling before changing\n* can use this if its not a long time\n\n\nBlack screen (of booked seats) <= for really\n* can use a virtual queue to dynamically allow interested users in\n\n1. too many fighting for the same seats (limited seat ~10k or smt)\n2. need to introduce a choke point\n3. virtual waiting queue\n    => can be a redis queue (lightweight)\n    => or redis sorted set (priority based on the person's arrival time)\n    => could be a random decision (make it such that ppl nearer our servers dont get priority)\n\n* make this event driven such that after first 100 seats booked, let the next 100 in etc.\n\n\n- all incoming traffic will hit queue service, it then issues queue token, position number, estimated wait time\n- admission controller then admits N user (based on system capacity) & issues them a short-lived purchase token\n    (JWT or some token containing eventId with expiration)\n- once admitted users can select seat & will upon reserving, will keep the seat as held until the purchase is completed",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "deep dive 2: scalability for popular events\n* take a step back & think about the perspective of users\n1. talk through what the client has to do when buying a ticket\n2. 1st instance is accurate representation of avail seats\n3. in a few moments, especially popz events, view can go stale quickly\n4. can make seat map availablity in real time\n\nin real time seat map\nsoln1: long polling\nkeep long polling the server\ncheap\nez to implement\nespecially when users are not on there for a long time (few seconds to mins)\n\nsoln2: SSE\nnot similar to implementation as long polling\nreduce the overhead of having to keep polling before changing\n* can use this if its not a long time\n\n\nBlack screen (of booked seats) <= for really\n* can use a virtual queue to dynamically allow interested users in\n\n1. too many fighting for the same seats (limited seat ~10k or smt)\n2. need to introduce a choke point\n3. virtual waiting queue\n    => can be a redis queue (lightweight)\n    => or redis sorted set (priority based on the person's arrival time)\n    => could be a random decision (make it such that ppl nearer our servers dont get priority)\n\n* make this event driven such that after first 100 seats booked, let the next 100 in etc.\n\n\n- all incoming traffic will hit queue service, it then issues queue token, position number, estimated wait time\n- admission controller then admits N user (based on system capacity) & issues them a short-lived purchase token\n    (JWT or some token containing eventId with expiration)\n- once admitted users can select seat & will upon reserving, will keep the seat as held until the purchase is completed",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
